articles.author: Sweta Goswami
articles.title: Baltimore bridge collapse incident unlikely to impact coal prices for India: Experts - Moneycontrol
articles.description: India primarily imports thermal coal from South Africa and Indonesia, and average prices from these countries decreased by approximately 54 percent and 38 percent respectively during April 2023 to January 2024 as against a year ago.
articles.content:
The collapse of a major Baltimore bridge on March 26 is unlikely to impact coal prices for India, according to industry experts.
